cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB. 

This paper is about developing an automatic approach for generating training data for event extraction, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves knowledge extraction from structured knowledge bases, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DB (Databases).
